  "text": "While systemic symptoms of amyloidosis are variable, cardiac findings are dominated by diastolic heart failure resulting from restrictive cardiomyopathy. Findings of right-sided heart failure predominate, including lower extremity edema, hepatomegaly, ascites, and elevated jugular pressure. [CITATION_1] A murmur may be present from valvular insufficiency, and atrial fibrillation is common.",
